    "notes": "Primary detection signal: process.executable path contains AppData\\Local\\Temp combined with rapid sequential outbound network connections (EID 3) to multiple ports on internal subnet hosts. Secondary signal: process.name 'task_scheduler.exe' making network connections is anomalous — the legitimate Windows Task Scheduler binary is svchost.exe-hosted and does not open raw TCP sockets. Tune out: nmap.exe from Program Files path, mstsc.exe to single RDP targets, and IT asset management tools (e.g., lansweeper, PDQ). Correlate EID 1 (process spawn) + EID 3 (network connect) on same PID within short time window for high-fidelity alert."
